The rate is expansive ( try special offers ) but it is a very Four Seasons with comfort and perfect service .	It has a beautiful and relaxing lobby, and very nice rooms, but other than that I was disappointed.	The hotel is modern and unlike most Four Season properties, but the rooms were quiet and peaceful.	This the kind of hotel that makes travelling the perfect mix of adventure and creature comforts.	We had drinks and snacks one evening in the ART bar, which was positively buzzing (it WAS Happy Hour) with a most convivial atmosphere.	All in all it was very relaxing to lounge by the pool, even with all of the kids splashing around in the pool.